                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <head>No. 89.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 23, 1884.</date> (Received February
                        9.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 486.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your telegram received January
                    2, requesting me to ask that the time allowed for the admission of American pork
                    in France be extended to the 1st of February, I have the honor to inform you
                    that the application was made and granted.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LEVI P. MORTON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
